'''Anthropomancy''' (from [[Greek language|Greek]] ''anthropos'' (''ἄνθρωπος'', man) and ''manteia'' (''μαντεία'', divination)) is a method of [[divination]] by the entrails of dead or dying men or women, often virgin female children, through sacrifice.{{Citation needed|date=April 2009}} This practice was sometimes also called '''splanchomancy'''. In ancient [[Etruria]] and [[Ancient Rome|Rome]], the usual variety of divination from entrails was haruspicy (performed by an [[haruspex]]), in which the sacrifice was an animal.

