{{Tengrianism}}
According to [[Tengrism|Turkic shamanism belief]], '''Kut''' is a kind of force vitalizing the body. Through Kut, humans are connected with the heavens. When Kut ends, the person dies. Further, the [[Khagan|sacred ruler]] is believed to be endowed with much more Kut than other people, thus the heaven would had appointing him as the legitimate ruler.<ref>JENS PETER LAUT ''Vielfalt türkischer Religionen'' p. 25  (German)</ref><ref>Carter Vaughn Findley ''The Turks in World History'' Oxford University Press 2004 {{ISBN|9780199884254}}</ref>

