The '''Lynch test''' is a consistency test of journalists covering the Israeli-Arab conflict.<ref name="nation0508">{{cite news|url=http://www.thenation.com/article/not-passing-israels-lynch-test|title=On Not Passing Israel's 'Lynch Test' |last=Eldar |first=Akiva |date=26 May 2008 |work=The Nation |accessdate=25 December 2009}}</ref><ref name="HtzFlu">{{cite news |url=http://www.haaretz.com/jewish-world/2.209/the-jew-flu-the-strange-illness-of-jewish-anti-semitism-1.267172 |title=The Jew Flu: The strange illness of Jewish anti-Semitism |last=Zilber |first=Uzi |date=1 January 2009|publisher=Haaretz |accessdate=25 December 2009}}</ref><ref name="JP0508">{{cite news |url=http://www.jpost.com/Features/Front-Lines/Between-the-Lines-Barbaras-audition-Rafis-sign-off-and-Akivas-confession |title=Between the Lines: Barbara's audition, Rafi's sign-off and Akiva's confession |last=Ben-David |first=Calev |date=15 May 2008 |publisher=The Jerusalem Post |accessdate=27 January 2014}}</ref> According to [[Nahum Barnea]], winner of the [[Israel Prize]], Israeli journalists who fail to criticize Arab terrorism fail the lynch test.<ref name="nation0508" /><ref name="HtzFlu" /><ref name="JP1007">{{cite news |url=http://www.jpost.com/Opinion/Op-Ed-Contributors/Shame-on-Haaretz |title=Shame on 'Haaretz' |last=Leibler |first=Isi |date=6 November 2007 |publisher=The Jerusalem Post |accessdate=27 January 2014}}</ref><ref name="Seliktar">{{cite book| last = Seliktar| first = Ofira Seliktar| title = Doomed to Failure?: The Politics and Intelligence of the Oslo Peace Process| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=26o_Qwy-KLkC&pg=PA103| year = 2009| publisher = ABC-CLIO| location = Page 95| isbn = 978-0-313-36617-8| pages = 238 }}</ref> According to author [[Kenneth Levin]], this is a "rare instance of Israeli media self-scrutiny."<ref name="Levin">{{cite book| last = Levin| first = Kenneth| title = The Oslo syndrome: delusions of a people under siege| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=Q4ttAAAAMAAJ| year = 2005| publisher = Smith and Kraus| location = Page 445| isbn = 978-1-57525-417-3| pages = 559 }}</ref> The term came after the [[2000 Ramallah lynching]], in which an Arab mob beat to death two Israeli reservists who had mistakenly entered Ramallah.<ref name="nation0508" /><ref name="HtzFlu" /><ref name="brutal">{{cite web |title= Lynch mob's brutal attack |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/969778.stm |date= 2000-10-13 |publisher=[[BBC News]] |accessdate=2014-01-27}}</ref>

